This help file explains each of the configuration parameters in your 
configuration .ini file.  It is broken up into sections that match the headers
in the configuration file.

=====================================
= 1. The [LmCompute - contact] section          =
= 2. The [LmCompute - environment] section      =
= 3. The [LmCompute - commands] section         =
= 4. The plugins sections:          =
=   4.1. The [LmCompute - plugins - openModeller] section =
=   4.2. The [LmCompute - plugins - maxent] section       =
= 5. The [LmCompute - options] section          =
= 6. The [LmCompute - metrics] section          =
=====================================

1. The [LmCompute - contact] section
========================
   INSTITUTION_NAME - The name of the institution running this installation.  
                         eg. University of Kansas - Biodiversity Institute 
   ADMIN_NAME - The name of the administrator of this machine
   ADMIN_EMAIL - The email address of the administrator
   LOCAL_MACHINE_ID - The name of this machine

2. The [LmCompute - environment] section
============================
   PLUGINS_PATH - The location of the plugins folder [/var/lm/LmCompute/plugins] 
   APP_PATH - The location of your application executables [/var/lm/apps/]
   JOB_DATA_PATH - Where to store input data [/var/lm/data/] 
   JOB_OUTPUT_PATH - Where to store job files [/var/lm/jobs/] 
   LM_USER_JOB - The Lifemapper user to run jobs for.  This can be a comma 
                    separated list [lm2]
   PYTHON_CMD - The path to the Python executable to use [python]
   TEMPORARY_FILE_PATH - A location to store temporary files [/var/lm/temp/]

3. The [LmCompute - commands] section
=========================
   GDALINFO_CMD - The path to the 'gdalinfo' command [gdalinfo]

4. The plugins sections
=======================

  4.1. The [LmCompute - plugins - openModeller] section
  ===============================
     DEFAULT_LOG_LEVEL - The default log level for openModeller [debug]
     OM_MODEL_CMD - The name of the openModeller modeling binary [om_model]
     OM_PROJECT_CMD - The name of the openModeller projection binary [om_project]
     OM_VERSION - The version of openModeller installed [1.3.0]

  4.2. The [LmCompute - plugins - maxent] section
  =========================
     JAVA_CMD - The command to run the java executable [java -cp]
     ME_CMD - The name of the Maxent jar file (in your applications directory) 
                 [maxent.jar]
     MDL_TOOL - The Maxent modeling tool [density.MaxEnt]
     PRJ_TOOL - The Maxent projection tool [density.Project]
     ME_VERSION - The version of Maxent installed [3.3.3k]
  
5. The [LmCompute - options] section
========================
     STORE_LOG_FILES - A boolean value indicating if log files should be 
                          collected [False]
     LOG_STORAGE_LOCATION - If log files are to be stored, they should be 
                               stored at this location []
                               
6. The [LmCompute - metrics] section
========================
     STORE_METRICS - A boolean value indicating if metrics should be collected 
                        [True]
     METRICS_STORAGE_PATH - The location to store metrics files 
                                    [/var/lm/metrics]
